text: The Berkeley Apartments is a historic three-story apartment building in Omaha, Nebraska. It was built by O.F. Nelson in 1915, and designed in an eclectic style with Prairie School features by H. D. Frankfurt. With By the 1990s, it was "one of the finest surviving examples" of buildings designed by Frankfurt. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since July 19, 1996. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Omaha, Nebraska Category:Residential buildings completed in 1915 Category:1915 establishments in Nebraska
